722395f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 112th Street
722395f-a.text:
1563-S
Park Pvenue, eest side between 112th and 113th Streets.
Notice Spanish sign on the poultry merket; the dominant elements in
the population hereabouts are Spanish, Jewish, end Negro.
August 31, 1929.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

715054f-a.text:
1O1-103 East 112th Street, at and adjoining the N.E. corner
of Park Avenue. No. 1Ol is a one-story frame shack and No. 103
is a two-story frame house.
February 27, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
